description.narrative: Most vulnerable and disadvantaged girls and boys have access to services to prevent and respond to violence against children, which contributes to Communication And Advocacy, Cross-Sectoral - Human Rights, Cross-Sectoral - Other Programme Areas, Prevention Of Harmful Practice, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, girls and boys in Ghana, especially the most disadvantaged, increasingly benefit from an equitable and integrated child protection system.

description.narrative: Social Service Workforce Strengthening and integrated social services initiatives (ISS) were scaled up to 100 districts out of 260. This also includes the roll-out of Primero-based Social Welfare Information Management System (SWIMS) in as many districts. Over 11082 children (girls7355, boys 3727) were reached with UNICEF supported multi-sectoral case management services in 100 districts. This was a result of joint initiative support by both child and social protection programmes in Ghana. Further, 143,221 adolescent girls were also reached with prevention and care services related to child marriage. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2021
